headline: Shopify Stock Falls on Earnings. Why Investors Aren’t Satisfied.
summary: Shopify’s  third-quarter earnings failed to satisfy Wall Street as investors looked beyond better-than-expected revenue and gross merchandise volume.  Revenue surged 32% to $2.84 billion in the quarter, topping the consensus call for $2.76 billion among analysts polled by  FactSet  Gross merchandise volume from merchant customers rose 32% to $92 billion, topping the 28% gain to $89.12 billion Wall Street had projected.  On the positive side, Shopify said Tuesday morning it expects revenue to grow “at a mid-to-high-twenties percentage rate.”

headline: Examining the Narrative for FactSet as Analyst Views Shift Amid Strategy Updates and AI Integration
summary: FactSet Research Systems’ fair value estimate has been lowered very slightly from $338.13 to $337.81 after the latest analysis, reflecting a minor adjustment of less than one dollar. This modest change comes as analysts weigh both the resilience of FactSet’s client relationships as well as the challenges posed by evolving industry trends and investments.
